	(13,1,'2014-08-04 16:12:44','2014-08-04 16:12:44','<h2>Looking to have fun while you train? Youve come to the right place!</h2>\r\nWe are serious about delivering top notch training programs that help you accomplish your athletic goals while keeping in mind that for sports to become part of your active and healthy lifestyle they have to be something you enjoy. TriLatino thrives in creating a supportive and caring atmosphere where perceived limits get challenged by coaches that want to get to know you by name, care about who you are, and what you are trying to do. During every training session, youll improve your skills, build endurance, and enjoy the support of your teammates who will sweat next to you and cheer you on to ensure you give it your best during each workout. Regardless of whether you are trying to shave minutes of your racing time or looking to conquer your first triathlon we are here to get you there.\r\n<h2>Dive into triathlon or simply focus on a single sport.</h2>\r\nWe have training options to match your preferences and needs. If you are looking to conquer a triathlon you can train for each discipline once a week (swim, bike run) or upgrade to our TriLatino Ms triathlon program which includes an additional core training session and detailed instructions on what you should be doing every day to complement coached sessions. If you decide you want to focus on a single discipline, we also have swim packages including a learn-to-swim track for those looking to get their feet wet and open water swims to build confidence outside the pool. Our run packages include running speed and endurance or marathon training. Our triathlon and individual disciplines programs start in spring (March) and winter (November) and our marathon program kicks off in the summer (July). Get the full details by checking out the program you are most interested on to the right.\r\n<h2>But its not just about training!</h2>\r\nOne of the biggest benefits of joining is getting to know your TriLatino family and making new friends. We organize monthly outings ranging from socials, team races and volunteer opportunities to encourage athletes to get to know each other in a more personal level. We are grateful for the friendships we continue to enable with every new training season. Attendance to these outings is not mandatory but highly encouraged to take advantage of the complete TriLatino experience.','Training','','publish','open','open','','training','','','2014-08-04 16:14:51','2014-08-04 16:14:51','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/trilatino/?page_id=13',0,'page','',0),
