	(44,1,'2014-08-04 16:18:35','2014-08-04 16:18:35','Last modified February 2014\r\n\r\nThis Privacy Policy and Notice (this Privacy Policy) is incorporated into the Terms of Use pertaining to your use of the website/s of TriLatino Triathlon Club, Inc.. The Terms of Use can be read by navigating to the appropriate link entitled, Terms of Use, on the Site. Capitalized terms used in this Privacy Policy, unless context requires otherwise, have the meanings given to them in the Terms of Use. This Privacy Policy applies only to information collected through the Site, not to information collected offline. By accessing, visiting or otherwise using the Site, you consent to this Privacy Policy and all of the other provisions of the Terms of Use. If we ever change any terms of the Privacy Policy, we will post those changes on this page. Accordingly, you agree to review this Privacy Policy each time you access, visit or otherwise use the Site.\r\n\r\n<strong>Your Privacy</strong>\r\n\r\nWe value your privacy. This Privacy Policy gives notice of and explains our practice of collecting information online and your participation about the way your information is collected and used by us.\r\n\r\n<strong>What Information Do We Collect?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe collect certain information from you when you either register to use the Site, when you fill out a form on the Site, when you order a product or service through the Site, or when you otherwise give information about you to us by means of the Site. The categories of personal information we collect on the Site include: your name; your address; your email address; your phone number; on pages where you are required or requested to make a payment to us, your credit card, debit card, charge card or bank account information; and, if the Site permits you to order product or pay for a service to be delivered to or otherwise used by another person, we may require you to provide one or more of the name, address, phone number and/or email address of any person to whom a product is to be delivered or by whom a service is to be provided.\r\n\r\n<strong>For What Purpose Do We Use You Information</strong>\r\n\r\nTriathlon Club Members. We use your information of members of our triathlon club to facilitate and efficiently provide information concerning club training and other activities, race information, informational opportunities, workshops, and other training and racing information. We may share contact information of the members of the club to the clubs coaches for purposes of their administration of the clubs coaching program and distribution from them of schedule and other training and coaching information.\r\n\r\nOrdering Products or Services. We use your information when you order a product or service to process the transaction. We do not share this information with outside parties except to the extent necessary to complete that order. We may also use this information to confirm deliveries of product orders if such orders are not delivered to us for subsequent distribution. We use the information you provide about someone else when placing an order as a gift only to ship the product and to confirm delivery. We do not share this information with outside parties except to the extent necessary to complete that order.\r\nNews re Charitable Events, Partners, Sponsors, Etc. We also use your information provide you with information that may be of interest concerning our charitable causes, our partners and sponsors and our fundraising events.\r\n\r\nWe may use information that neither identifies you nor discloses any personal or financial information of yours in order to better design our website, or to share with sponsors, partners or advertisers. For example, we may disclose to such a person that a certain number of users visited a certain area on our website without disclosing personal information about those users; we may disclose that a given number of men and women are members of our triathlon club, or that a certain number of mens clothing items or womens clothing items were ordered on the Site, but shall not disclose identifying information concerning those men and women or the persons making such product purchases.\r\n\r\nOther Uses. We may also use information we collect from time to time to personalize your experience with the Site; to improve the Site; to ensure quality control in services we provide; to send periodic emails to you; and/or to administer Site features.\r\n\r\nWe do not use or share the personally identifiable information provided to us online in ways unrelated to the ones described above without also providing you an opportunity to opt-out or otherwise prohibit such unrelated uses.\r\n\r\nYour information, whether public or private, will not be sold, exchanged, transferred or otherwise given to any other company for any reason whatsoever, without your consent, other than as expressly described herein.\r\n\r\n<strong>Data Security</strong>\r\n\r\nWhile no data security practice or procedure can be 100% foolproof, we have instituted physical, electronic and managerial procedures that we believe are appropriate and customary under current standards in order to secure personal information we collect on the Site and to prevent unauthorized access to such information and maintain data accuracy and ensure that we use information we collect correctly. We offer the use of third-party secure server processors, such as PayPal. After a commercial transaction, your private information that may have been required for such transaction (credit card numbers, social security numbers, financial information ) will not be stored.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do we use cookies?</strong>\r\n\r\nYes. A cookies is a file that, if you permit cookies, a website or service provider transfers to your computers hard drive by means of your Internet browser which enables the relevant system to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information. We use cookies to compile a