	(60,1,'2014-08-04 16:22:13','2014-08-04 16:22:13','<h2>Indoor Swim Training</h2>\r\n<strong>Get your feet wet and ready for open water!</strong>\r\nSwimming is  for most  the greatest challenge in entering the sport of triathlon. We provide athletes of all abilities with the opportunity to foster this important life skill. Our sessions will boost your confidence in the water by breaking down all of the technique you need to learn by levels of ability. We give you time to get down the fundamentals, such as breathing and feeling comfortable in the water, before diving into endurance and speed building techniques.\r\n\r\nChoose from one of four levels of ability as follows  all meet once a week:\r\n\r\n<strong>Learn to Swim</strong>\r\nLose your fear of the water this 2014! You know how important it is to be able to enjoy a pool or beach without having to worry about being safe. This session will teach you to breath, basic swim skills and get you comfortable being in the water. By the time the session ends you should be able to confidently get from a few pool laps in!\r\n\r\nLocation, day and time: Class meets at 58th Street and 10th Avenue on Thursdays at 8PM\r\n\r\n<strong>Beginner Swim</strong>\r\nGetting from one side of the pool to the next is no big deal, now let us help improve on your form and technique. This session will teach you proper swim skills and breathing. By the time you are done with this class you should be able to glide thru the water more efficiently and breathing under water should be second nature.\r\n\r\nLocation, day and time: Class meets at 47th Street and 3rd Avenue on Tuesdays at 9PM\r\n\r\n<strong>Intermediate Swim</strong>\r\nDesigned for swimmers who have their fundamentals down and now looking to finesse their technique to swim faster and longer. This session will help you build endurance, give you pointers towards transferring your skills into the open water and improve your coordination in the water.\r\n\r\nLocation, day and time: Class meets at 58th Street and 10th Avenue on Thursdays at 8PM\r\n\r\n<strong>Advanced Swim</strong>\r\nThis session is for strong swimmers looking to develop greater skill in the pool or open water. Most of the time during the session will focus on endurance swimming at a fast pace. We will help you tweak your form to develop greater comfort in your swim technique to challenge your personal best.\r\n\r\nLocation, day and time: Class meets at 47th Street and 3rd Avenue on Tuesdays at 8PM\r\n\r\n<strong>Details around swim sessions:</strong>\r\n\r\nCoaches will continuously monitor your progress and help you move into the next level of swim training.\r\n\r\nCourse duration: Twenty-six (26) swim sessions (all ability levels) starting March 4 - ending September 4 (no class July 3)\r\n\r\nProgram Cost: Twenty-six (26) sessions for $400* ($15.38 per class).\r\n* Payment plans available\r\n\r\nAt this time we are not registering any more athletes for our spring training session. For now, we invite you to register for our marathon (or simply running) program. <a title=\"Marathon\" href=\"http://spidadesign.us/trilatino/training/marathon/\">Check out the details</a>.','Indoor Swim','','publish','open','open','','indoor-swim','','','2014-08-04 17:44:41','2014-08-04 17:44:41','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/trilatino/?post_type=training&#038;p=60',0,'training','',0),
