	(120,1,'2014-08-04 17:10:02','2014-08-04 17:10:02','<strong>Triathlon Coach and Head Coach for TriLatino Junior</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coaching Experience: Over 6 years in triathlon and endurance sports. Founder and first coach of the Columbia University Triathlon Team.</li>\r\n	<li>Coaching Certifications and Training: USAT Level 1 certified triathlon coach, USAT Youth &amp; Junior Certified Coach, USA Cycling Level II Certified Cycling Coach, Certified POSE Method Instructor</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Experience: Joe grew up as a track and field athlete as well as a basketball player and later decided to channel his love for sports and competition through Triathlon. He has been competing in duathlons and triathlons since 1992 and has placed in a number of age group and</li>\r\n	<li>Clydesdale category races throughout the United States.</li>\r\n</ul>','Coach Joe','','publish','open','open','','coach-joe','','','2014-08-04 17:10:02','2014-08-04 17:10:02','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/trilatino/?post_type=coaches&#038;p=120',0,'coaches','',0),
	(121,1,'2014-08-04 17:10:44','2014-08-04 17:10:44','<strong>Triathlon Coach</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coaching Experience: Over 6 years in triathlon and long distance running, including coaching for Terrier Tri.</li>\r\n	<li>Coaching Certifications: Certified Personal Trainer and Fitness Instructor</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Experience: All American Scholar Athlete &amp; Wrestler, 9x Ironman Finisher, 15x Half Ironman Finisher, 2009 Ironman World Championship Finisher, 2012 US Ironman Championship Finisher, 2013 European Ironman Championship Finisher, 2014 USA Triathlon</li>\r\n	<li>Long Course World Championship Qualifier. Sponsored athlete by SLS3- Triathlon Gear and New York Health Racquet Club.</li>\r\n	<li>Outside Triathlon: Sam works as a corporate Director of NY Health &amp; Racquet Club (+35,000 members)</li>\r\n</ul>','Coach Sam','','publish','open','open','','coach-sam','','','2014-08-04 17:10:44','2014-08-04 17:10:44','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/trilatino/?post_type=coaches&#038;p=121',0,'coaches','',0),
	(122,1,'2014-08-04 17:11:33','2014-08-04 17:11:33','<strong>Triathlon Coach  Adult and Junior Team</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coaching Experience: Over 6 years coaching and mentoring athletes in triathlon and endurance sports. Thaddeus first started coaching/personal training in the U.S. Army as remedial fitness instructor for his unit in Germany, training soldiers recovering from injury or struggling with weight or performance goals.</li>\r\n	<li>Coaching Certifications: USA Triathlon Certified Coach (Level 1), USAT Youth &amp; Junior Certified Coach, NASM certified personal trainer, FIST certified bike fitter</li>\r\n	<li>Racing Experience: Thaddeus began racing on his company\'s cross-country team at the DOD\'s Defense Language Institute. He has raced numerous sprint, Olympic, 70.3 Half Ironmans and Kona Hawaii Ironman World Championships, and twice completed both the S.O.S. Triathlon, a grueling 8-stage adventure race in the Shawangunk mountain range, and the Death Valley Marathon twice. Thaddeus has completed over one hundred running races from 5k to marathon, and various open-water swim events.</li>\r\n	<li>Outside of triathlon: Thaddeus practices law and proudly numbers TriLatino among his clients. After receiving his undergraduate degree in International Business from Temple University, Thaddeus graduated from Notre Dame Law School, and is licensed in New York and California.</li>\r\n	<li>Other Highlights: TriLatino\'s first coach since the clubs founding in 2009.</li>\r\n</ul>','Coach Thaddeus','','publish','open','open','','coach-thaddeus','','','2014-08-04 17:11:33','2014-08-04 17:11:33','',0,'http://spidadesign.us/trilatino/?post_type=coaches&#038;p=122',0,'coaches','',0),
