	(400,1,'2014-08-07 17:16:07','2014-08-07 17:16:07','<div class=\"content clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\" style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-items\" style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">\r\n<div class=\"field-item even\" style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-weight: 500; font-style: inherit; color: #ef4056;\">Thanks for stopping by to learn about TriLatino Triathlon Club.</h2>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">We are a New York City 501(3) nonprofit organization with the mission of increasing the participation of Latinos in triathlon (swim, bike, run) and endurance sports, promoting healthy lifestyles, and uplifting our communities. Whether you are looking to learn the ropes or to perfect your skills, we offer a training environment where athletes of all abilities can thrive together. We train, compete and celebrate our accomplishments as a family. No one ever gets left behind.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"font-weight: 500; font-style: inherit; color: #ef4056;\">So you might ask, do I have to be Latino to join?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">No, you dont need to be Latino to join. Everyone is welcomed. All we ask is that you support our mission and have a lil bit of salsa in your soul! We are really proud of the diversity within our club. Last time we checked, we estimated that 60% of our athletes are Latino and 40% come from other ethnic backgrounds. But when we talk about diversity we dont just base it on ethnicity, we also enjoy a nearly 50/50 split between male and female athletes and our members ages range from the early twenties into the late 60s. Some compete in short sprint races, others go all out to the Ironman distance and others just join for fitness. This is just to say, that no matter who you are, there is a place for you within TriLatino.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"font-weight: 500; font-style: inherit; color: #ef4056;\">We not only train adults, we have a TriLatino Junior Team!</h2>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">As part of our efforts to uplift our communities by controlling the high incidence of diabetes, obesity and high cholesterol, amongst other epidemics, that affect our Latino neighborhoods, every year we invite 15 kids from the Bronx Academy of Letters (BAL) to explore the sport of triathlon. Through this after school program, we teach youth life skills, discipline to complete the goals they set out for themselves, teach them about proper nutrition, get them fit through weekly training sessions and, most importantly show them how all of these things add up to create a positive long term impact in their lives.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"font-weight: 500; font-style: inherit; color: #ef4056;\">Now that you know a little bit about us</h2>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;\">We invite you to learn more by befriend us on Facebook. Our athlete community is lively and active posting on our everyday accomplishments, big or small. We hope youll be one of them soon! For information on how to join the TriLatino family by register to one of our training programs, contact us at<a style=\"font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #ef4056;\" href=\"mailto:info@trilatino.org\">info@trilatino.org</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision-v1','','','2014-08-07 17:16:07','2014-08-07 17:16:07','',32,'http://trilatino.local/32-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
